Description: Egypt, adult male "warrior" wearing gown, shoes, trousers, bead necklace; holding circular shield and brandishing spear. Rural setting. Medium: Black and white. Gelatin silver print. Format: Print mounted on card.
Producer name: Photographed by: Captain Tristram C S Speedy
Curator's comments: Main Themes of Box: Rural life in Sudan, Ethiopia and Somaliland, including shelters, boat, shrine; paintings on exterior wall of a shelter; aerial photographs of a settlement; portraits of Somali chief and warrior. Warrior is Arab nomad. Suggested by E Kurimoto (NME, Osaka) 31/01/1996. Geography: Ethnic group suggested E Kurimoto, (NME, Osaka) 31/01/1996. Circumstances: [KUR-] PIC DOC 09. Af,9.13 depicts the same adult male in a similar pose.
